		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />HTTPS links to the root page of the wiki get redirected to an HTTP page, losing security:<br /><a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com" class="postlink">https://wiki.nesdev.com</a><br /><br />A direct link to any article, however, takes me to an HTTPS page as expected:<br /><a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev" class="postlink">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev</a><br /><br />I presume that whatever's at the root page contains a hardcoded redirect to <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev_Wiki" class="postlink">http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Nesdev_Wiki</a> rather than something that preserves the security protocol?

		

